  "an11.502-981:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 11.502–981 ",
  "an11.502-981:0.2": "The First Fifty ",
  "an11.502-981:0.3": "Similarity ",
  "an11.502-981:0.4": "Untitled Discourses on the Eye, Etc. ",
  "an11.502-981:1.1": "“Mendicants, a cowherd with eleven factors can maintain and expand a herd of cattle. ",
  "an11.502-981:1.2": "What eleven? ",
  "an11.502-981:1.3": "It’s when a cowherd knows form … ",
  "an11.502-981:2.1": "In the same way, a mendicant with eleven qualities can meditate observing impermanence in the eye … ",
  "an11.502-981:2.2": "",
  "an11.502-981:2.3": "meditate observing letting go. …” ",
  "an11.982:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 11.982 ",
  "an11.982:0.2": "The First Fifty ",
  "an11.982:0.3": "Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed ",
  "an11.982:0.4": "Untitled Discourse on Greed ",
  "an11.982:1.1": "“For insight into greed, eleven things should be developed. ",
  "an11.982:1.2": "What eleven? ",
  "an11.982:1.3": "The first, second, third, and fourth absorptions; the heart’s releases by love, compassion, rejoicing, and equanimity; the dimensions of infinite space, infinite consciousness, and nothingness. ",
  "an11.982:1.4": "For insight into greed, these eleven things should be developed.” ",
